{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"2e751fd5-1430-4a2f-b731-2a4db5876423","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, tasks.md under specrunner/changes/init-reports-scaffold/ on branch change/init-reports-scaffold-ae96b6a9.\n\nDesign summary:\n- D1: git repo check becomes the first gate in runInit — before global config resolution and provider prompt. Not a git repo / git binary unavailable → logError prescription to stderr + return 1, nothing written (including global config). No auto `git init`.\n- D2: item-by-item report to stdout via logResult (NOT logSuccess/logInfo which go to stderr). Four labels — `global config`, `.gitignore`, `specrunner/drafts`, `specrunner/changes` — each `created` | `already exists`. Removes \"Config saved.\" / \"Config already exists. Skipping...\" lines.\n- D3: created/exists detection per item — config via existing configExists flag; .gitignore via changing ensureDotSpecrunnerGitignore return from Promise<void> to Promise<boolean> (additive, existing gitignore tests unchanged); drafts/changes via fs.mkdir(recursive) return value (path=created, undefined=exists).\n- D4: exit 1 for environment error, keep exit 2 for deprecated --runtime arg error.\n\nTasks T-01..T-05 cover gitignore return change, runInit gate+report rewrite, README Quick Start git-repo precondition, test updates (flip existing TC-002 into T1 with destructive check, add T2/T3/T4), and verification (typecheck && test). Noted that cwd-unmocked config tests stay green because the test process cwd is a git worktree.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-20T03:30:18.084Z","endedAt":"2026-07-20T03:37:14.538Z","commitOid":"43396ce625e3c19da3c344d0c33215e3f4c2488e"}
